{
  "title": {
    "text": "The operating system must install security-relevant\n                        software updates within the time period directed by an authoritative\n                        source (e.g., IAVM, CTOs, DTMs, and STIGs).",
    "lang": "en"
  },
  "description": {
    "text": "Security flaws with operating\n                        systems are discovered daily. Vendors are constantly updating\n                        and patching their products to address newly discovered security\n                        vulnerabilities. Organizations (including any contractor to the\n                        organization) are required to promptly install security-relevant software\n                        updates (e.g., patches, service packs, and hot fixes). Flaws discovered\n                        during security assessments, continuous monitoring, incident response\n                        activities, or information system error handling must also be addressed\n                        expeditiously.",
    "lang": "en"
  },
  "rationale": {
    "text": "Chainguard images contain only the minimal software needed for\n                        the container to perform its intended function. Non-essential capabilities\n                        such as software installers, shell environments, executables, and process\n                        launching functions have been removed from the images and may not be\n                        installed once the container is running.\n\n                        The limited implementation enables only the necessary software to operate\n                        on the running container and restricts the installation of additional\n                        software on the image during operating. For applying security relevant\n                        updates, up-to-date Chainguard images need to be incorporated into the\n                        operating environment through some form of automation or other event\n                        aware process to ensure concurrency with the latest available version.\n\n                        For more information on inherited controls for containers see the DISA\n                        Container Hardening Process Guide.",
    "lang": "en"
  },
  "platform": {
    "idref": "cpe:/o:notapplicable"
  },
  "ident": {
    "text": "CCI-002605",
    "system": "http://cyber.mil/cci"
  },
  "id": "xccdf_mil.disa.stig_rule_SV-259333r958940_rule",
  "selected": "true",
  "role": "full",
  "severity": "medium"
}

