{
  "title": {
    "text": "The operating system must synchronize internal\n                        information system clocks to the authoritative time source when the time\n                        difference is greater than one second.",
    "lang": "en"
  },
  "description": {
    "text": "Inaccurate time stamps make it more difficult to\n                        correlate events and can lead to an inaccurate analysis. Determining the\n                        correct time a particular event occurred on a system is critical when\n                        conducting forensic analysis and investigating system events.\n\n                        Synchronizing internal information system clocks provides uniformity of time\n                        stamps for information systems with multiple system clocks and systems\n                        connected over a network. Organizations should consider setting time periods\n                        for different types of systems (e.g., financial, legal, or mission-critical\n                        systems).\n\n                        Organizations should also consider endpoints that may not have regular\n                        access to the authoritative time server (e.g., mobile, teleworking, and\n                        tactical endpoints). This requirement is related to the comparison done\n                        every 24 hours in SRG-OS-000355 because a comparison must be done in order\n                        to determine the time difference.",
    "lang": "en"
  },
  "rationale": {
    "text": "Linux containers inherit the system time from the underlying host\n                        - a separate time service is not operated within the container. The host\n                        owner is responsible for configuring the host's time service to generate the\n                        timestamp used by its auditing system, perform periodic synchronization, and\n                        ensure that only authorized time servers are used as the authoritative\n                        source. Time synchronization of the host clock is automatically reflected in\n                        the time used by the container.\n\n                        For more information on inherited controls for containers see the DISA\n                        Container Hardening Process Guide.",
    "lang": "en"
  },
  "platform": {
    "idref": "cpe:/o:notapplicable"
  },
  "ident": {
    "text": "CCI-004926",
    "system": "http://cyber.mil/cci"
  },
  "id": "xccdf_mil.disa.stig_rule_SV-203712r982209_rule",
  "selected": "true",
  "role": "full",
  "severity": "medium"
}

