{
  "title": {
    "text": "The operating system must control remote access\n                        methods.",
    "lang": "en"
  },
  "description": {
    "text": "Remote access services, such as those providing\n                        remote access to network devices and information systems, which lack\n                        automated control capabilities, increase risk and make remote user access\n                        management difficult at best. Remote access is access to DoD nonpublic\n                        information systems by an authorized user (or an information system)\n                        communicating through an external, non-organization-controlled network.\n                        Remote access methods include, for example, dial-up, broadband, and\n                        wireless. Operating system functionality (e.g., RDP) must be capable of\n                        taking enforcement action if the audit reveals unauthorized activity.\n                        Automated control of remote access sessions allows organizations to ensure\n                        ongoing compliance with remote access policies by enforcing connection rules\n                        of remote access applications on a variety of information system components\n                        (e.g., servers, workstations, notebook computers, smartphones, and tablets). <html:pre xmlns:html=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">\n                        Script Verification:\n                            To manually verify, Ensure none of the following remote access packages\n                        exist in the folder /lib/apk/db/ Packages:\n                            openssh, openssh-server, openssh-client, openssh-sftp-server, dropbear,\n                        tigervnc, tigervnc-server, tigervnc-viewer,\n                            xrdp, xorgxrdp, vsftpd, proftpd, webmin, cockpit, cockpit-ws,\n                        cockpit-bridge, nfs-utils, samba, samba-server, samba-client, samba-common,\n                        rsh, telnet\n                        </html:pre>\n                    ",
    "lang": "en"
  },
  "ident": {
    "text": "CCI-002314",
    "system": "http://cyber.mil/cci"
  },
  "check": {
    "check-content-ref": {
      "href": "RemoteAccessServicesTest.xml"
    },
    "system": "http://oval.mitre.org/XMLSchema/oval-definitions-5"
  },
  "id": "xccdf_mil.disa.stig_rule_SV-203686r958672_rule",
  "selected": "true",
  "role": "full",
  "severity": "medium"
}

